p: The six-month chart review revealed that among participants with available data, 91.6% (98/107) completed the entire nPEP regimen, and 36.0% of all patients (67/186) attended at least one follow-up appointment three months post-enrolment or later. One individual tested HIV positive at baseline, only 16 hours post-exposure, indicating seroconversion resulted from a previous exposure. The other 98.4% (61/62) of participants tested at 12 weeks post-exposure remained HIV negative.
